2. Calculate Electricity BillQuestionWrite a Java program to calculate an electricity bill using a standard tiered tariff system:First 100 units: ₹1.5 per unitNext 100 units (101-200): ₹2.5 per unitNext 100 units (201-300): ₹4.0 per unitAbove 300 units: ₹6.0 per unitCodeJavaimport java.util.Scanner;

public class ElectricityBill {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter total units consumed: ");
        double units = scanner.nextDouble();

        double billAmount = 0;

        if (units <= 100) {
            billAmount = units * 1.5;
        } else if (units <= 200) {
            billAmount = (100 * 1.5) + ((units - 100) * 2.5);
        } else if (units <= 300) {
            billAmount = (100 * 1.5) + (100 * 2.5) + ((units - 200) * 4.0);
        } else {
            billAmount = (100 * 1.5) + (100 * 2.5) + (100 * 4.0) + ((units - 300) * 6.0);
        }

        System.out.printf("Total Electricity Bill: ₹%.2f\n", billAmount);
        scanner.close();
    }
}
Output:
Enter total units consumed: 250
Total Electricity Bill: ₹600.00


